title: Person In Motorized Wheelchair Dark Skin Tone
alsoKnownAs: Person in motorized wheelchair (dark skin tone)
description: Represents a person using a motorized wheelchair, specifically with a dark skin tone. It signifies mobility, independence, and accessibility, often used in discussions about disability or personal experiences.
apple_vendor_description: On Apple devices, the person in a motorized wheelchair with dark skin tone is rendered with a rich, deep complexion and a confident posture. The electric wheelchair itself boasts smooth, rounded edges and subtle reflections, indicative of Apple's signature glossy 3D shading. This emoji conveys independence, accessibility, and the joy of movement, often used to represent personal experiences or support for disability inclusion on Apple devices.
